article.headline: Rider 58, Binghamton 50
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. -- Ryan Thompson scored 12 of his 21 points in the final 6 minutes and Rider rallied to defeat Binghamton 58-50 on Saturday night. The Broncs (4-3) were 8-for-32 in the first half, including 0-for-12 from 3-point range, to fall behind 25-20 at halftime. Trailing 31-20 with 17:02 to go, Rider used a 10-0 run to tie the game with 14:41 left. The Broncs and Bearcats stayed within three points of each other until Thompson hit two straight layups with 1:34 left to make it 54-48. Thompson and Justin Robinson added two free throws apiece in the last 53 seconds. Rider shot 34.4 percent from the field (21-for-61) for the game, compared to 52.4 percent (22-for-42) for Binghamton. The Broncs shot 7-for-11 from beyond the arc in the second half. Jhamar Youngblood added 10 points. Umur Peten scored 14 points for the Bearcats (2-5), including nine in the first half.
